// go.work — the Go workspace file. It is the "root" of local development.
//
// A workspace lets multiple modules on disk resolve each other directly,
// without `replace` directives or publishing to a remote. Every module we
// build gets added here with `go work use ./services/<name>`. For now there
// is only the shared module.
//
// go.work is intentionally NOT committed in some teams (it's a local-dev
// convenience). We commit it here because the repo IS the workspace: the
// monorepo and the workspace are the same thing for this project.

// Bumped from 1.23 -> 1.25 because google.golang.org/grpc (v1.81+) now requires
// Go >= 1.25, and a workspace's go directive must be >= every module it uses.
// We have Go 1.26 installed, so this costs us nothing.
go 1.25.0

use (
	./pkg
	./proto
	./services/hello
)
